    <note>Zhan(1) Kangzong [13438] He is listed as a Kuaiji (Shaoxing-s) person in the Zhejiang TZ, 125.13a and as Linzong's [13437] elder brother in Liangzhe jinshi zhi, 10.25b, but as a Shanyin resident in CBD and therefore as such in the 1148 jinshi list. I keep as a Shanyin resident since this is the benguan of record for other Shaoxing Zhan. Recheck other cases where office-holding is associated with the residence of an important lineage of the same surname, but different address (e.g. in this case Chu(c)zhou), which adds to the evidence that the Suian, Chongan and Shanyin Zhan are all related. CBD, 5, 3277From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1170:  Apt. prefect of Chu(c)zhou.</note>
